	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=12664><span id= >shyft</span></a><br><span id=notbold>229 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.35]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>It doesn't suck, why is it 50pp on every server I've checked?<br><br>It's a mystery to me...it can't be THAT easy to obtain.<br><br>I think this one item has skewed the entire 2HB market, and the whole weapon market to some degree. If it weren't warrior-only, just imagine the stuff you could buy for double digits. :)<br><br>Blunt or slahing, 2H is 2H, and 30/40 is a damn nice ratio for mere mortals. That's a 75% ratio. It'll outdamage a pair of 50% ratio one-handers until you've levelled into the 50s and spent some AA on dual-wield. You'll certainly be hitting hard enough to keep aggro on under-40 mobs, if the ranger doesn't insist on getting it.<br><br>At level 20 (when the damage cap goes away), it's the best 50pp you'll ever spend! You'll be godlike at 20, and set for the next 20+ levels if you want. You can even be a soloing warrior, if you want. I did that with a 28/45 Mithril Staff, back when, and went from 25 to 32 damn fast. If I hadn't needed to practice up 2HB from around 40, it would have been even faster. I scrimped, saved and killed an ASSLOAD of wisps and bandits for that weapon. Paid 700pp, a good price in those days. Now these are 50 plat! People still want more for the Mithril Staff (Good luck).<br><br>A 30/40 weapon would have been even sicker and wronger (in a good way hehe), in the hands of a warrior in their 20s.<br><br>So again, why is it so extremely cheap? One of life's little mysteries.<br><br><br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
